children.name: Design token automation from Figma to Storybook
children.characters: Design token automation from Figma to Storybook

children.name: This is a companion Figma file used in my blog post around design token automation. If you want to follow along with the post, it outlines the steps for automating a workflow that reads & writes Figma Token values stored in a Github repository, transforming the tokens using token transformer and style dictionary, and outputting css variables that are used in a stencil web component and storybook documentation. The Figma token file used is available on github. You can save a local copy and load it into Figma Tokens if you want to play around.
